{"name":"Mathlib.Logic.Function.Basic","instances":[{"typeNames":["Eq"],"name":"Function.decidable_eq_pfun","className":"Decidable"},{"typeNames":[],"name":"Function.HasUncurry_base","className":"Function.HasUncurry"},{"typeNames":["Prod"],"name":"Function.HasUncurry_induction","className":"Function.HasUncurry"}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Logic.Basic","Mathlib.Init.Data.Nat.Lemmas","Mathlib.Init.Function","Mathlib.Init.Set","Mathlib.Init.SetNotation","Mathlib.Tactic.Lint.Basic"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L664-L665","name":"set.separates_points","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#set.separates_points","doc":"A set of functions \"separates points\"\nif for each pair of distinct points there is a function taking different values on them. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L655-L658","name":"set.piecewise","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#set.piecewise","doc":"`s.piecewise f g` is the function equal to `f` on the set `s`, and to `g` on its complement. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L646-L648","name":"Function.sometimes_spec","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.sometimes_spec","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L643-L644","name":"Function.sometimes_eq","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.sometimes_eq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L640-L641","name":"Function.sometimes","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.sometimes","doc":"`sometimes f` evaluates to some value of `f`, if it exists. This function is especially\ninteresting in the case where `α` is a proposition, in which case `f` is necessarily a\nconstant function, so that `sometimes f = f a` for all `a`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L629-L630","name":"Function.injective2.eq_iff","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.injective2.eq_iff","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L626-L627","name":"Function.injective2.right","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.injective2.right","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L623-L624","name":"Function.injective2.left","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.injective2.left","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L617-L618","name":"Function.injective2","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.injective2","doc":"The property of a binary function `f : α → β → γ` being injective.\nMathematically this should be thought of as the corresponding function `α × β → γ` being injective.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L608-L610","name":"Function.involutive.eq_iff","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive.eq_iff","doc":"An involution commutes across an equality. Compare to `function.injective.eq_iff`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L603-L606","name":"Function.involutive.ite_not","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive.ite_not","doc":"Involuting an `ite` of an involuted value `x : α` negates the `Prop` condition in the `ite`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L601-L601","name":"Function.involutive.bijective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive.bijective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L600-L600","name":"Function.involutive.surjective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive.surjective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L599-L599","name":"Function.involutive.injective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive.injective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L597-L597","name":"Function.involutive.RightInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive.RightInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L596-L596","name":"Function.involutive.LeftInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive.LeftInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L593-L594","name":"Function.involutive.comp_self","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive.comp_self","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L587-L588","name":"Function.involutive_iff_iter_2_eq_id","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive_iff_iter_2_eq_id","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L585-L585","name":"Function.involutive","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.involutive","doc":"A function is involutive, if `f ∘ f = id`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L579-L580","name":"Function.HasUncurry_induction","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.HasUncurry_induction","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L577-L577","name":"Function.HasUncurry_base","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.HasUncurry_base","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L575-L575","name":"Function.«term↿_»","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.«term↿_»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L569-L570","name":"Function.HasUncurry","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.HasUncurry","doc":"Records a way to turn an element of `α` into a function from `β` to `γ`. The most generic use\nis to recursively uncurry. For instance `f : α → β → γ → δ` will be turned into\n`↿f : α × β × γ → δ`. One can also add instances for bundled maps. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L558-L560","name":"Function.uncurry_bicompl","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.uncurry_bicompl","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L555-L556","name":"Function.uncurry_bicompr","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.uncurry_bicompr","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L553-L553","name":"Function.«term_∘₂_»","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.«term_∘₂_»","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L549-L550","name":"Function.bicompr","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.bicompr","doc":"Compose an unary function `f` with a binary function `g`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L545-L546","name":"Function.bicompl","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.bicompl","doc":"Compose a binary function `f` with a pair of unary functions `g` and `h`.\nIf both arguments of `f` have the same type and `g = h`, then `bicompl f g g = f on g`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L536-L538","name":"Function.curry_apply","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.curry_apply","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L532-L534","name":"Function.uncurry_apply_pair","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.uncurry_apply_pair","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L529-L530","name":"Function.uncurry_def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.uncurry_def","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L523-L525","name":"Function.extend_comp","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.extend_comp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L518-L521","name":"Function.extend_apply","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.extend_apply","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L513-L516","name":"Function.extend_def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.extend_def","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L510-L511","name":"Function.extend","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.extend","doc":"`extend f g e'` extends a function `g : α → γ`\nalong a function `f : α → β` to a function `β → γ`,\nby using the values of `g` on the range of `f`\nand the values of an auxiliary function `e' : β → γ` elsewhere.\n\nMostly useful when `f` is injective. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L491-L494","name":"Function.update_idem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_idem","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L479-L489","name":"Function.update_comm","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_comm","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L475-L477","name":"Function.comp_update","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.comp_update","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L468-L473","name":"Function.apply_update","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.apply_update","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L462-L466","name":"Function.update_comp_eq_of_injective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_comp_eq_of_injective","doc":"Non-dependent version of `function.update_comp_eq_of_injective'` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L457-L460","name":"Function.update_comp_eq_of_injective'","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_comp_eq_of_injective'","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L451-L455","name":"Function.update_comp_eq_of_forall_ne","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_comp_eq_of_forall_ne","doc":"Non-dependent version of `function.update_comp_eq_of_forall_ne'` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L446-L449","name":"Function.update_comp_eq_of_forall_ne'","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_comp_eq_of_forall_ne'","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L443-L444","name":"Function.update_eq_self","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_eq_self","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L439-L441","name":"Function.eq_update_iff","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.eq_update_iff","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L435-L437","name":"Function.update_eq_iff","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_eq_iff","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L414-L433","name":"Function.forall_update_iff","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.forall_update_iff","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L410-L412","name":"Function.update_noteq","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_noteq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L405-L408","name":"Function.update_injective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_injective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L402-L403","name":"Function.update_same","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_same","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L391-L400","name":"Function.update_apply","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update_apply","doc":"On non-dependent functions, `function.update` can be expressed as an `ite` "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L388-L389","name":"Function.update","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.update","doc":"Replacing the value of a function at a given point by a given value. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L378-L380","name":"Function.surjective_to_subsingleton","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.surjective_to_subsingleton","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L375-L376","name":"Function.injective_surj_inv","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.injective_surj_inv","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L371-L373","name":"Function.bijective_iff_has_inverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.bijective_iff_has_inverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L368-L369","name":"Function.surjective_iff_has_RightInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.surjective_iff_has_RightInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L365-L366","name":"Function.surjective.has_RightInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.surjective.has_RightInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L362-L363","name":"Function.LeftInverse_surj_inv","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.LeftInverse_surj_inv","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L359-L360","name":"Function.RightInverse_surj_inv","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.RightInverse_surj_inv","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L357-L357","name":"Function.surj_inv_eq","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.surj_inv_eq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L355-L355","name":"Function.surj_inv","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.surj_inv","doc":"The inverse of a surjective function. (Unlike `inv_fun`, this does not require\n`α` to be inhabited.) "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L345-L346","name":"Function.injective_iff_has_LeftInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.injective_iff_has_LeftInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L342-L343","name":"Function.injective.has_LeftInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.injective.has_LeftInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L335-L335","name":"Function.inv_fun_comp","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.inv_fun_comp","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L332-L333","name":"Function.inv_fun_surjective","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.inv_fun_surjective","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L328-L330","name":"Function.LeftInverse_inv_fun","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.LeftInverse_inv_fun","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L325-L326","name":"Function.RightInverse_inv_fun","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.RightInverse_inv_fun","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L320-L323","name":"Function.inv_fun_eq_of_injective_of_RightInverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.inv_fun_eq_of_injective_of_RightInverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L317-L318","name":"Function.inv_fun_neg","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.inv_fun_neg","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L313-L315","name":"Function.inv_fun_eq","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.inv_fun_eq","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.lean#L311-L311","name":"Function.inv_fun","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Function/Basic.html#Function.inv_fun","doc":"The inverse of a function (which is a left inverse if `f` is injective\nand a right inverse if `f` is s